 910.0]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [795.7, 893.7, 818.6, 913.6]}, {"text": "158.8", "bbox": [838.4, 893.7, 871.2, 910.0]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [896.7, 893.7, 919.5, 913.6]}, {"text": "196.8", "bbox": [939.4, 893.7, 972.2, 910.0]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [997.6, 893.7, 1020.5, 913.6]}, {"text": "(38.0)", "bbox": [1046.8, 890.9, 1100.2, 913.6]}, {"text": "(19)%", "bbox": [1135.9, 893.7, 1172.4, 910.0]}, {"text": "Effective tax rate", "bbox": [78.1, 921.3, 177.8, 937.3]}, {"text": "25.7 %", "bbox": [431.2, 921.3, 472.5, 937.3]}, {"text": "20.4%", "bbox": [539.2, 918.3, 610.2, 941.1]}, {"text": "20.4%", "bbox": [845.7, 918.3, 901.1, 941.1]}, {"text": "63.1%", "bbox": [946.7, 918.3, 1017.6, 941.1]}, {"text": "Interest income primarily includes interest income from our cash, cash equivalents, and investments. Interest expense increased in 2011, compared to 2010,", "bbox": [75.0, 966.9, 1177.1, 986.7]}, {"text": "primarily due to the $37.7 million interest expense on the debt issued in March 2011. Other typically consists of investment and foreign exchange gains and", "bbox": [75.0, 988.2, 1179.7, 1008.0]}, {"text": "losses and other non-operational income and expense items. In 2011, other included certain legal expenses unrelated to current or recent operations of", "bbox": [75.0, 1009.4, 1136.8, 1029.2]}, {"text": "approximately $7.0 million . In 2010, we recognized a total gain of $8.7 million, primarily due to acquisitions of our privately-held equity investments in", "bbox": [75.0, 1030.7, 1160.1, 1050.5]}, {"text": "Ankeena and Altor. During 2009 we recognized an impairment loss of $5.5 million on our equity investments for changes in fair value that we believed were", "bbox": [75.0, 1051.9, 1189.0, 1071.7]}, {"text": "other-than-temporary.", "bbox": [75.0, 1073.2, 230.9, 1093.0]}, {"text": "Our effective tax rates were 25.7%, 20.4%, and 63.1% in 2011, 2010, and 2009, respectively. The effective rate for 2011 differed from the federal statutory", "bbox": [75.0, 1115.7, 1176.1, 1135.5]}, {"text": "rate of 35% primarily due to the federal R&D credit and the benefit of earnings in foreign jurisdictions, which are subject to lower tax rates. The effective tax", "bbox": [75.0, 1136.9, 1190.9, 1156.7]}, {"text": "rate for 2011 differed from 2010 as a result of the items referenced below, which were recognized in 2010.", "bbox": [75.0, 1158.2, 831.3, 1178.0]}, {"text": "The decrease in overall rate in 2010 compared to 2009, and the federal statutory rate of 35%, was primarily due to the federal R&D credit, the benefit of", "bbox": [75.0, 1200.7, 1154.0, 1220.5]}, {"text": "earnings in foreign jurisdictions, which are subject to lower tax rates, and a $54.1 million income tax benefit in 2010 resulting from a change in the", "bbox": [75.0, 1221.9, 1117.7, 1241.7]}, {"text": "Company's estimate of unrecognized tax benefits due to the taxpayer favorable ruling by the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit (the “Court”) in", "bbox": [75.0, 1243.2, 1157.2, 1263.0]}, {"text": "Xilinx Inc. v. Commissioner related to share-based compensation.", "bbox": [75.0, 1264.4, 538.3, 1284.2]}, {"text": "The effective tax rate in 2009 was higher than the federal statutory rate of 35% primarily due to the following income tax charges: (i) a $61.8 million discrete", "bbox": [75.0, 1307.1, 1190.4, 1326.8]}, {"text": "and other related charge that resulted from changes in California income tax laws that were enacted during 2009; (ii) a $52.1 million charge that resulted from", "bbox": [75.0, 1328.3, 1195.3, 1348.1]}, {"text": "a change in our unrecognized tax benefits related to share-", "bbox": [75.0, 1349.6, 488.6, 1369.3]}, {"text": "42", "bbox": [628.7, 1388.5, 646.4, 1408.3]}]}